<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-359-214  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 359 214.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  April 16 1990 v36 n1805 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Urge probe of Japan HDTV access. (high definition television)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robertson,,Jack.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Trade negotiators in the US are requesting that the JapaneseMinistry of International Trade and Industry investigate chargesby National Semiconductor and other US firms that they are beingexcluded from the Japanese high-definition television market(HDTV).andP;  A senior trade official reports that the US continues tobe disappointed about the low number of semiconductor sales.andO;Japan is feeling great pressure to increase its purchases of USsemiconductors, under the US-Japan Semiconductor Arrangement thatexpires in mid-1991.andP;  Meanwhile, National Semiconductor iscomplaining about Japanese firms that are refusing to talk withthe company about design-ins for planned HDTV sets.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     High definition televisionTradeMarket ShareJapanese CompetitionSemiconductor industry.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>